What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A great course, and definitely one to take in the HSHM department if you are interested in epidemiological history. Be prepared to actively engage in seminar and also undertake a great deal of independent research.
It is an interesting take on a seminar since you follow a disease for an entire semester but there is a good deal of reading and not too much direction.
